to the editor joyce purnick metro matters column dec 6 suggests that to lead new york mayor elect michael r bloomberg must reveal details of his private life as proof mayor rudolph w giuliani 's practices are presented as the foundation for his acceptance as a reassuring leader on and after sept 11 but it is not what we know about the mayor 's private life that allows him to connect with us so powerfully at this harrowing time it is his strong leadership his compassion and his feelings for the tragedy 's effect on new yorkers pressuring our leaders to reveal their private thoughts and moments does not serve the public interest it is important that we know their views about public issues not where they spend their vacations invasive questions about private matters deter exceptional people from public service arthur j fried executive director center for excellence in new york city governance nyu new york dec 10 2001

